{
  "stem": "13469.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So basically, the war lasted only five days because the Germans bombed Rotterdam.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They flattened Rotterdam.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they threatened to do the same to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So Holland capitulated, partly also because of all this intrigue behind the lines.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The, the Dutch apparently flooded a large area of Holland in order to stop the invasion.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the Germans had already got to the other side of it by all these Fifth Columnists and the paratroopers, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the Dutch defense plan just didn't work at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when they threatened to flatten Amsterdam by bombing it, like they'd done in Poland, all that sort of thing, the Dutch gave up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And within five days, they capitulated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Germans took charge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is, of course, when all the trouble started.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I gather that many people did try and get away, get out of Holland, get to England in those days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I can't remember us making any attempt like that at all.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for, for a time, I suppose, at first, life went on as, as before.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we didn't really feel the Nazi rules.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it, it was quite strange that one of the first effects that, that we had on these racial laws-- of which there were more and more could have come later on-- there was one law, which I've never, ever seen mentioned by anybody.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was the one that affected us at first, within six months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was that Jews were not to live-- not allowed to live by the seaside.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was obviously because the Germans were starting to build fortifications there in order to repel the British or attack England or something.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
